          },
          "content": "### What this dashboard covers\n\nThis dashboard queries the boxel database directly via the **boxel-db** Postgres datasource \u2014 no `pg_exporter` needed.\nInspired by the upstream [PostgreSQL Monitoring Dashboard](https://grafana.com/grafana/dashboards/24298-postgresql-monitoring-dashboard/) but trimmed to what operators act on.\n\n### Not covered (would require additional tooling)\n\n- **Slow-query analysis** \u2014 needs the `pg_stat_statements` extension (not currently enabled). When enabled, panels for top queries by total time / mean time / I/O become possible.\n- **WAL throughput, replication lag, FPI ratio** \u2014 needs `pg_exporter` to expose these as Prometheus metrics. Boxel's Postgres is RDS with no exporter sidecar today.\n- **Bloat estimation** \u2014 needs `pgstattuple` extension. Approximated here by `n_dead_tup / n_live_tup`.\n\n### Drill-through\n\n- Each long-running or idle-in-txn entry shows the `pid` \u2014 paired with the realm-server / worker logs (via the **Logs** dashboard) you can correlate the SQL to the request that issued it.\n",
          "mode": "markdown"
        },
